omic redistribution, scientific expertise, and national identity as a way to create compliance among the country's most vulnerable rural residents. In this way, Leguizamón demonstrates that GM soy operates as a tool of power to obtain consent, legitimate injustice, and quell potential dissent in the face of environmental and social violence.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aAgricultural biotechnologyxEnvironmental aspectszArgentina. 0aAgricultural biotechnologyxSocial aspectszArgentina. 0aEnvironmental policyzArgentina. 0aGenetically modified foodsxSocial aspectszArgentina. 0aSoybeanxGenetic engineeringxEnvironmental aspectszArgentina. 0aTransgenic plantsxEconomic aspectszArgentina. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  apesticide drift.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069631808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478012375zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478012375423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781478012375.jpg  a978-3-11-069631-8  DUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-SEWb2020